  <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Start at 18g in and 36g out, then target roughly 25 to 32 seconds. If the shot runs fast and tastes sour, go slightly finer; if it runs slow and tastes bitter, go slightly coarser. Keep dose and yield fixed while dialing grind size so every change is clear.</p>

