  <h2 id="what-youll-need">What you'll need</h2>
  <p>Before you change settings, set up a stable process. You need fresh beans, a digital scale, a consistent puck prep routine, and a grinder that can hold a precise espresso range. If your grinder steps are too wide, you can still dial in good shots, but the process takes more back-and-forth. Precision matters most when coffee ages across the week and your recipe drifts.</p>

